{
  "stem": "10588.12",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Bianco. ?] And here was-- what I have memories is that during Passover, because we kept the Jewish tradition and laws, we didn't-- we only ate matzo for Passover.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't' eat bread, according to the Jewish tradition.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was the-- when Passover was over, there used to be a long line of people.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They-- and they used to buy bread.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because everybody, after not eating eight days bread, everybody was longing for eating bread.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I remember as a child, we used to come here and have bread.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And one thing was funny, that sometimes on the road, people were so anxious that they would take off a little piece and eat it before they even brought it home.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And now, this-- nobody lives here.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's empty.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there are very few Jewish houses and no Jewish people left here-- none.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Everything was wiped off.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "However, further down, there is a building, a huge building comparing to-- in the-- in comparison to the others, which still is the original building from before the war.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was a [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Do you want to tell the story now?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Wooden homes, and one of was our home, I believe.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But there's none.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They are torn down because all the wooden buildings are torn down.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So the [INAUDIBLE], where I lived the last few years when Germany came in, before Germany came in, I no longer see here.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was right next to the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So when we get there, I'll show you.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "OK?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Thank you.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[SPEAKING NON-ENGLISH] OK.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This is the building where there was the [INAUDIBLE] and the drugstore.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there was a lot of Jewish people living in this building.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And when the Nazis came, came in and they started to bombard because, you know, the war was going on, I remember my family came here to hide in the cellar.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we lived-- when you turn my hand from the back around this area.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But all the wooden house, houses, that were standing are no longer existed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They were torn down.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But I remember that all we had to do to go out from our house-- and it was near [INAUDIBLE] street.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So it's between when you now, all you see there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "This is where we lived.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And here, we were hiding.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then when the, when the Nazis took Poland, Warsaw, in 19-- September 1, 19-- September 28, 1939, after that time, we could no longer move-- go from place to place.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "That was the last time where I could walk freely or go to, go to visit my family, my friends, my relative.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We were [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I'm not going to elaborate, because I spoke about it before.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Because this is when they started the actual destructions here.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "So my family, my aunt, my mother's sister, Siri--, Shmuel Pazdziorek, [INAUDIBLE] [INAUDIBLE] Ester [INAUDIBLE] Shmuel Pazdziorek also lived in Ciechanow, Poland, not far from here.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And they were the parents of seven children, six daughters and one son.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Fortunately, in 19-- wait a second-- 1934, when I was eight years old, my cousin, who met a young man also native of Ciechanow, Poland-- and they fell in love.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "He, [?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Chaim ?] [INAUDIBLE] emigrated with the first Maccabiah to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I think it must have been about 1932, and at that time was Palestine.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Later, when he got a little established, she left.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And I remember the whole family gathered.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And everybody was crying and saying, God knows when we can see each other again.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And my grandmother, who was a woman of deep faith, said children, please don't cry.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "With God, all things are possible.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And because my cousin [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Ito, ?] named of the same great-grandmother-- the same name, the same birthplace-- left Ciechanow, Poland, she was the only one out of seven children that survived.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And she could never come back to Ciechanow, Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "There is no more Jewish, Jewish Ciechanow.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "How sh-- this river is called [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Ladinya ?] in Ciechanow, Poland.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when I was a child, we used to come here very often, many different capacities.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "People came here, some to bait.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Here, no father, there was-- people came Saturday after they came form the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they had the meal.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They used to take a rest.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then towards in the evening, before they went to the synagogue again, they would come here.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it would be like a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "An avenue where young boys and girls would meet, where parents and children would walk.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I remember very often holding my father's, my mother's hand and walking here.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this is where I used to play, as I told you before.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I used come to play here.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
